<meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css"/>
</head>
<body>
<p></span><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:13pt"><b>Tasks-&#160; Add</b></span></font><font color="#010101"></font></p>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">You can use this function to add new Tasks for your firm.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Name</b>: Enter the Unique name for the Task to be created (Ex : Seek Clarification- Utility Bill July 
2015)</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Description</b>: Enter the Description for the new Task you wish to create (Ex: Check with 
Authorities on the excess charges in the Utility Bill for July 2015)</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Due Date</b>: Choose the Date and time duration (from the Calendar utility) by when this Task needs 
to be accomplished.&#160; </span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Tags</b>: Add Tags to this Task (Ex: Urgent)</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Documents</b>: If you wish to attach relevant documents (Ex : Utility Biill in this case) for this task, 
click on the +<b>Upload</b> Button. Clicking this button, will open the Windows file selection dialog box. 
Choose the relevant document and click Open button. </span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Reminders</b>: Use this function to set reminders for the task. As the name suggests, these 
reminders will provide reminder alerts at the defined time to ensure that the tasks are completed 
on time.&#160; Click on <b>+Add </b>Button to start defining reminders. On clicking the <b>+Add</b> button, will open 
the Reminder definition window. </span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Type :</b> Choose the type of the reminder from the dropdown list. (Ex: Minutes before, hours before 
etc). Choose the relevant value based on whether you want these reminders to appear minutes 
before or hours before the <b>Due Date </b>defined for the task. This way the timely reminder ensures 
that you complete the task before the Due date. </span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt"><b>Value </b>: Enter the Value for the chosen type (Ex : If you have chosen <b>Minutes Before </b>and wish to 
be alerted or reminded 15 minutes before the Due Date and time of the task,&#160; then enter <b>15 </b>in the 
<b>Value </b>field.</span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">This way you can define more than 1 reminder. You can use the <b>Delete </b>Button if you wish to 
remove any of the reminders. </span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></span></font><font face="Arial" color="#010101"><span style="font-size:10pt">Finally choose <b>Finish </b>Button if you wish to save the added Task, else choose the <b>Cancel </b>Button if 
you wish to ignore the Task created.&#160; </span></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
<div align="left"><br />
</div>
<font color="#010101">
<div align="left"></font><font color="#010101"></font></div>
</body>
